{"body": "\"Probably the best way to fix is this is by moving the load_generators code from Application to Engine and call it on the engine. We could probably do the same for console and make rails console also work for engines.\"\r\n\r\nYeah, sounds like a nice solution! BTW, any plans to enable running executables such as _bundle_ and _rails_ within a dummy application in a project? \r\n\r\nCurrently this doesn't work, hence it's complicated to set up a dummy app for testing purposes - you first have to export it out, run your bundle/rails commands, then import the project back into your test folder :(\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/kristianmandrup/multiapp-engine", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1241824", "created_at": "2011-05-26T12:05:26Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/1327#issuecomment-1241824", "updated_at": "2011-05-26T12:05:26Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 1327, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kristianmandrup/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kristianmandrup/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kristianmandrup/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/kristianmandrup", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kristianmandrup/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/kristianmandrup", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kristianmandrup/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/2a018f8b16a3fe7273afde907c2e1bec?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fee7d0a95c98df729c5ab7c93d1df3aa9.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kristianmandrup/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kristianmandrup/received_events", "gravatar_id": "2a018f8b16a3fe7273afde907c2e1bec", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kristianmandrup/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "kristianmandrup", "type": "User", "id": 125005, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/use